---
import SiteLayout from "../components/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Astropress Operations"
  description="Astropress ships local operational guidance for doctor checks, backup and restore, and secret management. Hosted recovery remains an explicit limitation."
  heading="Use doctor, backup, and restore as first-class operational workflows."
  currentPath="/operations"
>
  <section class="panel-grid">
    <article class="panel">
      <h2>Core checks</h2>
      <p>
        Run <code>astropress doctor</code> before local launches and before releases. It should catch missing secrets,
        weak defaults, missing local data paths, and missing <code>ASTROPRESS_APP_HOST</code>,
        <code> ASTROPRESS_CONTENT_SERVICES</code>, or <code>ASTROPRESS_SERVICE_ORIGIN</code> settings early.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="panel">
      <h2>Backup and restore</h2>
      <p>
        Use <code>astropress backup</code> and <code>astropress restore</code> for local content and config snapshots.
        Treat hosted restore and rollback procedures as explicit follow-up work, not solved problems.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="panel">
    <h2>Release honesty</h2>
    <p>
      Astropress should document operational gaps plainly. Hosted secret rotation, hosted rollback procedures, and
      staging-backed incident drills are still limitations rather than marketing bullets.
    </p>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
